race.comment: KING OF THE JUNGLE (3) saluted in a CL4 at Sunshine Coast two runs ago. Fair effort there last time out when headed late in stronger beaten 2.4L. Will skip across and has the class to take this out. RED BOOMSHAKALAKA (5) went close at Warwick and the longer sprint will not be an issue. On an 8-day return and draws handy. The 3kg claim brings her right into it. SUTHERLAND (6) missed a nose this track and trip and then finished with the above at Warwick. Should enjoy a decent run and keeps the handy 2kg claim. TOYGER (9) is free running and bounced straight back into the winner's circle winning at Glen Innes. Jumps from a low gate and shouldn't be taken lightly.
